# UI Design Rules

All RepoPilot UI must follow this design language. Aesthetic reference: **Linear**, **Vercel**, **GitHub**, **Notion**.

## Layout

- **Prefer Card Layout** over long Markdown walls. Break content into scannable cards with clear sections.
- **Never duplicate layouts.** Extract shared structure into reusable components before adding to a page.
- **Every new feature → reusable component first.** Do not embed feature UI inline in `page.tsx` when it can be a component.

## Visual Hierarchy

Use three levels consistently:

| Level | Use |
|-------|-----|
| **Primary** | Titles, key actions, main metrics |
| **Secondary** | Supporting labels, section headers |
| **Muted** | Hints, metadata, timestamps, placeholders |

## Spacing & Surface

- **8px grid** for padding, margin, and gap (`8`, `16`, `24`, `32`…).
- **Rounded corners** on cards and interactive elements.
- **Soft shadows** for elevation — subtle, not heavy.
- **Modern typography** — clear weight/size scale; minimal decoration.

## Component Checklist

Before shipping UI:

- [ ] Content uses cards, not unstyled markdown blocks
- [ ] Layout lives in a reusable component under `frontend/src/components/`
- [ ] Primary / Secondary / Muted hierarchy is obvious
- [ ] Spacing aligns to 8px grid
- [ ] Styling matches existing RepoPilot patterns (rounded, soft shadow, minimal chrome)

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Pasting long AI Markdown directly without card/section structure
- ❌ Copy-pasting the same JSX layout in multiple files
- ❌ One-off page-only UI that should be a component
- ❌ Inconsistent spacing or competing visual weights
